casebody.data:
Baldwin, Respondent, v. Thibadeau, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

March 17, 1892.)

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Bischoff and Pryor, JJ.

W. Parker, for appellant. 8. F. Higgins, for respondent.

Ho opinion. Motion for reargument denied, but appellant may have leave to appeal to the court of appeals, if she desires so to do. See 14 N. Y. Supp. 788; 17 N. Y. Supp. 532.
